Package com.experian.aperture.datastudio.sdk.step

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    Cache
    The interface to be used to create/modify/delete a persistent global key/value datastore for use by an SDK step.
    StepColumn
    A basic interface for wrapping user-defined and internally defined Columns
    StepPropertyValidator
    For internal use only.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Column
    A basic class representing a user-defined column It can be used directly in custom steps, but it is recommended that non-advanced users use the Column object instead.
    ColumnManager
    Represents a list of a step's outputColumns, and exposes methods to aid the manipulation of them.
    StepConfiguration
    Metadata class that defines a step.
    StepOutput
    A base class that handles everything around the output of the step.
    StepProperty
    Class that represents a single step property - an item displayed in the UI within the step's panel, either displaying information about the step, or allowing the user to configure it.
  • Enum Summary 
    Enum Description
    ButtonConfiguration
    For internal use only.
    StepPropertyType
    StepPropertyTypes that are used to define the type of a step property StepPropertyType.BOOLEAN StepPropertyType.STRING StepPropertyType.INTEGER StepPropertyType.DECIMAL StepPropertyType.COLUMN_CHOOSER StepPropertyType.INPUT_LABEL
    StepPropertyType.MultiColumnType
